# Card-audit (mtg-948 Part B): Braingeyser — target player draws X (scripted).
#
# Closed issue mtg-488 closed Braingeyser as WORKING but carried NO scripted
# puzzle with semantic assertions (only a parser-shape unit test). This audit
# puzzle SCRIPTS the X-cost cast and asserts the draw-X outcome.
#
# Braingeyser is a {X}{U}{U} sorcery: "Target player draws X cards."
# (A:SP$ Draw | NumCards$ X | ValidTgts$ Player; SVar:X:Count$xPaid). X is locked
# from the mana paid on cast (CR 107.3, 601.2b). Here P0 has 4 Islands, so paying
# {X}{U}{U} funds X=2, and the target player draws 2 (CR 120.2).
#
# Aspects exercised (issue mtg-488):
#   1. Parses + castable as a {X}{U}{U} sorcery (spell cast assertion).
#   2. X is funded from mana paid: 4 Islands -> {2}{U}{U} -> X=2.
#   3. Draw effect moves exactly X=2 cards library -> hand for the target player
#      (here the caster P0, whose hand starts empty besides Braingeyser).
#
# Scenario:
#   - P0: Braingeyser in hand, 4 Islands (funds X=2 + {U}{U}), a library whose
#     top two cards (last two listed) are distinct, named Moxen.
#   - Script: P0 casts Braingeyser targeting itself; draws the top two cards.

[metadata]
Name:Card Audit - Braingeyser Draws X
Goal:Win
Turns:1
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 scripts Braingeyser ({X}{U}{U} sorcery) targeting itself with 4 Islands (X=2). It draws the top two library cards (Mox Sapphire then Mox Emerald) into hand. Backs issue mtg-488 (SP$ Draw NumCards$ X over Count$xPaid; CR 120.2).

[state]
turn=1
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=Braingeyser
p0battlefield=Island;Island;Island;Island
# The loader treats the LAST entry as the top of the library: the two drawn
# cards are Mox Sapphire then Mox Emerald.
p0library=Swamp;Swamp;Swamp;Swamp;Swamp;Swamp;Forest;Plains;Mountain;Mox Emerald;Mox Sapphire

p1life=20
p1battlefield=
p1library=Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain

[p0_script]
# Cast Braingeyser at P0 itself. With 4 Islands the engine pays {2}{U}{U} (X=2),
# drawing the top two library cards. Then PASS for the rest of the game so the
# drawn Moxen are not played out (keeps the hand-membership assertions durable).
cast Braingeyser targeting p1
PASS_UNTIL turn=5,phase=MAIN1

[p1_script]
# P1 takes no proactive action either.
PASS_UNTIL turn=5,phase=MAIN1

[assertions]
# The X-cost draw sorcery was actually cast.
spell cast Braingeyser
# Braingeyser itself is in P0's graveyard after resolving (sorcery -> GY).
graveyard contains Braingeyser
# P0 drew at least X=2 cards: hand has >= 2 (durable lower bound — P0 passes).
hand count ge 2
# The two top-of-library cards (X=2) were drawn into hand and stay there.
hand contains Mox Sapphire
hand contains Mox Emerald
